CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 23, 1951, pg. 2, reads: "Council Candidate Congratulated - Robert L. Carter, chairman of the committee which circulated petitions to place the name of Houston Dargan, cab driver and former steelworker, on the ballot of the Independent party for the general election in November, is shown congratulating Mr. Dargan after petitions insuring that both the party and Mr. Dargan's name will appear were filed recently. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robert L. Carter shaking hands with Independent party City Council candidate Houston Dargan, in Harris Studio
